title: PPPP’s M. Taimur Talpur  wins PS-51 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Muhamad Taimur Talpur has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-51, Umerkot-3 by securing 58,958 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Irshad Dost Muhammad of the Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged 27,725 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 48 %.
